(WEEK8 TEAM5 DB API CODE FLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This PDF summarizes which entry point runs, how the server starts,) Tj
T*
(and how one request travels across our files.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. ENTRY POINTS) Tj
T*
( - src/app/main.c               : local SQL CLI program) Tj
T*
( - src/app/sqlapi_server_main.c: API server entry point) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When we run ./build/bin/sqlapi_server, the active main\(\) is) Tj
T*
(src/app/sqlapi_server_main.c, not src/app/main.c.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. BIG PICTURE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Client) Tj
T*
(  -> sqlapi_server_main.c) Tj
T*
(     -> server.c) Tj
T*
(        -> accept thread) Tj
T*
(           -> task_queue.c) Tj
T*
(        -> worker_pool.c) Tj
T*
(           -> worker thread) Tj
T*
(              -> http/router.c) Tj
T*
(                 -> api/health_handler.c) Tj
T*
(                 -> api/query_handler.c) Tj
T*
(                    -> service/db_service.c) Tj
T*
(                       -> engine/sql_engine_adapter.c) Tj
T*
(                          -> engine/engine_lock_manager.c) Tj
T*
(                          -> parser / executor / storage / index) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key idea:) Tj
T*
(The app layer starts the runtime, server.c orchestrates threads and sockets,) Tj
T*
(and the engine layer reuses the existing SQL processor.) Tj
ET
